Document: KinematicCollision3D
Path: godot/classes/class_kinematiccollision3d.rst
Summary: Provides information about collision results when using KinematicBody3D.

Inherits: RefCounted

This object is returned by CollisionObject3D.move_and_collide and CollisionObject3D.test_move. It contains information about the collision that occurred.

Properties:
collision_normal (Vector3): The normal of the collision. This is the direction the object would need to move to resolve the collision.
collider (Object): The object that the body collided with.
collider_length (float): The length of the collider's shape that was hit.
collider_shape (int): The index of the shape that the body collided with on the collider.
collider_shape_owner (Object): The owner of the collider shape that was hit.
get_collider_velocity (Vector3): Returns the velocity of the collider at the point of collision.
local_shape (int): The index of the shape on the body that collided.
position (Vector3): The point in space where the collision occurred.
remainder (Vector3): The remaining distance the body can travel after the collision.
travel (Vector3): The distance the body traveled before the collision.
---CHUNK---
